How a Real Quote Session Works in LangGraph

    Tradie sends /new → New graph instance created with unique thread_id (quote ID).
    Every message from WhatsApp triggers app.invoke() or app.astream() with the new input.
    LangGraph automatically:
        Loads latest state from Supabase
        Runs the appropriate nodes
        Saves checkpoint after each major step
    Fine-tuning loop is just an edge that routes back to the draft node.
    Human review uses interrupt_before=["pdf"] so a reviewer can jump into the same thread.

Key Advantages for This Project

    Reliability — No more “lost context” between messages.
    Scalability — Each quote runs independently (great for concurrency).
    Debugging — LangSmith shows exactly which node failed and why.
    Personalisation — RAG node is called on every draft, pulling the tradie’s private data.
    Future-proof — Easy to add new nodes later (e.g., “auto-send to customer”, “Xero export”, “win/loss analysis”).

